This topic describes how to install and configure Altoros Elasticsearch for VMware Tanzu.

##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure Altoros Elasticsearch for VMware Tanzu

1. Download the product file from Pivotal Network.

1. Navigate to the **Ops Manager Installation Dashboard** and click **Import a Product** to upload the product file.

1. Under the **Import a Product** button, click **+** next to the version number of Altoros Elasticsearch for VMware Tanzu.
This adds the tile to your staging area.

1. Click the newly added **Altoros Elasticsearch for VMware Tanzu** tile.

1. Set up the network for the tile:
  <%= image_tag("images/networks.png") %>

1. Click **Save**.

1. You can disable node.data role for masters if you want to store data only on node vms (enabled by default):
<p class="note warning"><strong>Warning:</strong> Be carefull with this option. If you want to disable node.data role for master, scale your worker nodes before disable accordinlly.</p>
  <%= image_tag("images/settings.png") %>

1. Leave **First Install** check box for initial cluster setup and uncheck it immediately after installation completed.
<p class="note warning"><strong>Warning:</strong> Do not scale out or scale in your cluster during version upgrade from 1.1.4 to 1.1.5.</p>

1. Health check timeout is the time that bosh will wait before run monit stop during update or stop lifecycle. Default is 3000 seconds.

1. Click **Save**.

1. Return to the **Ops Manager Installation Dashboard**

1. Click **Review Pending Changes**

1. **Select PAS** this will update diego cells with dns alias and **Altoros Elasticsearch for VMware Tanzu**.
